    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1963-03-29T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1963-03-29T23:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <head>70. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Vietnam</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d70fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>(US) <gloss target="#t_S1"
                            >S</gloss> VIET. Secret; Limit Distribution. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <placeName>Saigon</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                                when="1963-03-30T12:00:00+08:00">March 30, 1963, noon</date>
                        </hi>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>860. <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1"
                        >POLAD</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_DEPTEL1">Deptel</gloss> 911<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d70fn2">
                        <ref target="#d69">Document 69</ref>.</note> greatly appreciated. If
                        <persName corresp="#p_THUAN1">Thuan</persName> has been unable to overcome
                    main objection to counterinsurgency fund described <gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 852<note n="3" xml:id="d70fn3">
                        <ref target="#d68">Document 68</ref>.</note> on basis arguments already
                    advanced, warnings and assurances contained <gloss target="#t_REFTEL1"
                        >reftel</gloss> should be most useful in my next meeting with him, <persName
                        corresp="#p_NHU1">Nhu</persName> or <persName corresp="#p_DIEM1"
                        >Diem</persName>. To make point even more emphatic, plan tell them also that
                    further procurement and shipment of hamlet kit materials (barbed wire,
                        etc.),<gloss target="#t_PL1">PL</gloss> 480 and <gloss target="#t_AID1"
                        >AID</gloss> dollar procurement items for hamlets would not seem justified
                    unless there is adequate piaster fund to go with them, and agreed procedures for
                    their effective use.</p>
                <p>Harkin and Brent concur.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_NFEJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Nolting</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
